hI RJ I know less than nothing, I&#39;ve never used a box, wanted to for a 
long time but I neither have the skills nor know-how to do so. What I do 
have is an open mind and inquisitive one at that.  I tend to believe 
that there is something as a Psychic of over 35+ years I&#39;ve seen and 
heard many things that defy logic and imagination. The notion that this 
may be quantified excites me!

So if you will help me out as noob, why &#39;would or could&#39; there be one 
voice; and conversely why &#39;would or could&#39; there be multiple voices.

I am genuinely interested in why you feel one way and Frank (I believe) 
feels the other? It helps me understand.

Deb






On 1/8/2010 7:48 PM, Rj wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Hi Deb.  I&#39;m not trying to make any claims: I&#39;m trying to determine 
&gt; what the claims are for the Frank&#39;s box.  And so I was asking the 
&gt; creator of the Frank&#39;s box, and then summarizing.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; --- On *Fri, 1/8/10, Debra Yeung /&lt;debra.yeung@...&gt;/* wrote:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;     From: Debra Yeung &lt;debra.yeung@...&gt;
&gt;     Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] Re: What does it do?
&gt;     To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
&gt;     Date: Friday, January 8, 2010, 4:28 PM
&gt;
&gt;     Hi Raster:
&gt;     I don&#39;t even rate tinkerer, I am a lurker  I do have a question
&gt;     why do you say that it be only one voice?
&gt;     Deb
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;     On 1/8/2010 7:05 PM, Frank Sumption wrote:
&gt;
&gt;&gt;      I&#39;m no expert, just a tinker-er, and my apologies for getting
&gt;&gt;     snippedy! There&#39;s just as many ways for the entities to make
&gt;&gt;     their voices as there is entities--there is no one/right
&gt;&gt;     way/explanation.
&gt;&gt;      F-S
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;     On Thu, Jan 7, 2010 at 2:28 PM, Rj &lt;rasterer@yahoo. com
&gt;&gt;     &lt;/mc/compose?to=rasterer@...&gt;&gt; wrote:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;         Thanks Tom for your comments.  You say that different people
&gt;&gt;         listening to the recordings often here the same thing.  But
&gt;&gt;         Frank says that is rarely the case.  Wouldn&#39;t Frank be more
&gt;&gt;         of the expert here?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;         --- On *Thu, 1/7/10, Tom /&lt;Tom_Ray@deq. state.ms. us
&gt;&gt;         &lt;/mc/compose?to=Tom_Ray@...&gt;&gt;/* wrote:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             From: Tom &lt;Tom_Ray@deq. state.ms. us
&gt;&gt;             &lt;/mc/compose?to=Tom_Ray@...&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: What does it do?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
&gt;&gt;             &lt;/mc/compose?to=EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt;
&gt;&gt;             Date: Thursday, January 7, 2010, 11:57 AM
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             The fact that the operator CAN and DOES make recordings
&gt;&gt;             and files of understandable words and phrases shows that
&gt;&gt;             we are dealing with an OBJECTIVE rather than a subjective
&gt;&gt;             phenomenon here. Two things appear to be going on though.
&gt;&gt;             First there is an actual voice modulated signal.
&gt;&gt;             Different people who listen to it often hear the same
&gt;&gt;             thing. The sound is not perfect and is very noisy, so
&gt;&gt;             that would explain others who cannot hear the message.
&gt;&gt;             The second thing is that some people can listen to the
&gt;&gt;             noise as a &quot;random field&quot;, and with a slightly altered
&gt;&gt;             state of mind, this field will induce latent &quot;mediumship&quot;
&gt;&gt;             ability in the operator and he or she will get a lot more
&gt;&gt;             information and voice material than another listener.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             Note that the content random fields have little or
&gt;&gt;             nothing in common with whatever imagery or sounds may be
&gt;&gt;             percieved from them. They simply enhance the user to
&gt;&gt;             access psychic information that, while even not being a
&gt;&gt;             &quot;psychic&quot; allows him to get info normally innaccessable
&gt;&gt;             to him/her.
&gt;&gt;             If there is any objective percieved sound similar to what
&gt;&gt;             is heard by others impressed upon the background noise,
&gt;&gt;             it might be due to the spirit who is speaking being
&gt;&gt;             PRESENT. That entity would then be able to get the
&gt;&gt;             message through to the operator Psychicly on another
&gt;&gt;             level. that the words are also in the noise would be a
&gt;&gt;             co-incidence.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             I work with VISUAL random fields---The imagery, while
&gt;&gt;             clear, is formed in my mind/eye system , so I cannot
&gt;&gt;             photograph it. Some of this EVP background noise may be
&gt;&gt;             working the same way too---formed in the Mind/EAR system.
&gt;&gt;             This is only heard by the primary operator and likely
&gt;&gt;             cannot be recorded to a file.
&gt;&gt;             But some random field stuff IS objective--for example,
&gt;&gt;             using a random backdrop for ghost photos makes the ghosts
&gt;&gt;             easier to, and more often appear in a photo. This is
&gt;&gt;             equavalent to the EVP that people can hear on the
&gt;&gt;             recorded file.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             I will discuss and explain random field theory itself,
&gt;&gt;             later, in its own posting.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
&gt;&gt;             &lt;http://mc/compose?to=EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt;, Zack
&gt;&gt;             Widup &lt;w9sz.zack@. ..&gt; wrote:
&gt;&gt;             &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; Just a guess, since I don&#39;t have a lot of experience
&gt;&gt;             with this - probably
&gt;&gt;             &gt; the mesages are meant for one user and it&#39;s best if one
&gt;&gt;             user listens at a
&gt;&gt;             &gt; time.
&gt;&gt;             &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; It could be that some messages come through that are
&gt;&gt;             meant for multiple
&gt;&gt;             &gt; users at once. I&#39;ve heard the same things as Frank in
&gt;&gt;             some of the recordings
&gt;&gt;             &gt; he&#39;s posted. FWIW.
&gt;&gt;             &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; Zack
&gt;&gt;             &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; On Thu, Jan 7, 2010 at 12:51 PM, Rj &lt;rasterer@.. .&gt; wrote:
&gt;&gt;             &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; Thanks Zack. So how do you see not asking it
&gt;&gt;             questions squaring with
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; Frank&#39;s comment of &quot;It&#39;s not the device, it&#39;s the
&gt;&gt;             user. The messages
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; received are for the user, and rarely does anyone
&gt;&gt;             hear the same thing as the
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; original listener.&quot;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; Does that mean two people can&#39;t use it together? How
&gt;&gt;             would they know which
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; the message was for if they do? Or is it best to only
&gt;&gt;             use it alone?
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; --- On *Thu, 1/7/10, Zack Widup &lt;w9sz.zack@. ..&gt;* wrote:
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; From: Zack Widup &lt;w9sz.zack@. ..&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] What does it do?
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com
&gt;&gt;             &lt;http://mc/compose?to=EVP-ITC%40yahoogroups.com&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; Date: Thursday, January 7, 2010, 10:40 AM
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; I don&#39;t think any of us know really who or what the
&gt;&gt;             &quot;entities&quot; are. They
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; have told a few people who they are, but given the
&gt;&gt;             propensity of some to
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; lie, who knows?
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; I also believe you do not need to ask any questions
&gt;&gt;             at all - just let the
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; box run and listen to what comes out, maybe record it
&gt;&gt;             at the same time so
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; you can replay it later.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; Zack
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; On Thu, Jan 7, 2010 at 12:10 PM, Rj &lt;rasterer@yahoo.
&gt;&gt;             com&lt;http://mc/compose? to=rasterer@ ...
&gt;&gt;             &lt;http://mc/compose?to=rasterer@...&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt; &gt; wrote:
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; Perhaps I am not being clear. I am not asking how it
&gt;&gt;             works. I am
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; asking what you claim it does.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; For example, from your statements below, I get:
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; &quot;The Frank&#39;s box allows entities to use FM and AM
&gt;&gt;             radio broadcast as raw
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; material, which these enties select and shape to
&gt;&gt;             communicate with the user.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; The messages received are for the user, and rarely
&gt;&gt;             does anyone hear the same
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; thing as the original listener.&quot;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; Can you be any more specific as to what you mean by
&gt;&gt;             &#39;entities&#39;?
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; Also, can the user be defined as the person asking
&gt;&gt;             the box questions?
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] What does it do?
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups .com&lt;http://mc/compose?
&gt;&gt;             to=EVP-ITC@ yahoogroups. com
&gt;&gt;             &lt;http://mc/compose?to=EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; Date: Thursday, January 7, 2010, 9:35 AM
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; It&#39;s a freaking radio! The tuning is swept across
&gt;&gt;             the entire band, AM or
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; FM, the resulting bits of speech, music, and noise
&gt;&gt;             are used by the enitites
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; as a raw material to build their voices from. The
&gt;&gt;             sweep can be linear,
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; random, or manual, and it does not have to cover the
&gt;&gt;             entire broadcast band.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; This is one method and device for providing the raw
&gt;&gt;             audio, and if you&#39;re
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; tesitng to see if it&#39;s just broadcast fragments,
&gt;&gt;             consider this-the concept
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; is the same as EVPmaker, EVPmaker runs on a
&gt;&gt;             computer, the entities
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; manipulate that raw audio *inside* the conmputer,
&gt;&gt;             and if you think stray
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; RF is going to get *inside* the hard drive and mix
&gt;&gt;             with the audio file
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; you have no clue how any technology works.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; Testing is irrelavent! It&#39;s not the device, it&#39;s the
&gt;&gt;             user. The messages
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; received are for the user, and rarely does anyone
&gt;&gt;             hear the same thing as the
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; original listener.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; You test it by use, you judge it by what comes
&gt;&gt;             through and what it means
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; to you, you can&#39;t play the sound snipets to a panel
&gt;&gt;             of numbnuts(objective
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; listeners)) and expect to get an unbiased/honest
&gt;&gt;             test. No two people hear
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; the same, so an &quot;objective listener&quot; is an insult to
&gt;&gt;             most people doing this
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; work.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; I know, I&#39;m being harsh.
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;             &gt; &gt;&gt; Frank-S
&gt;&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; 


